# TypeScript Pre-Commit Check

This project uses TypeScript project references. The root `tsconfig.json` has `"files": []`.

**NEVER** run `npx tsc --noEmit` alone — it compiles zero files and always exits 0, giving a false clean signal.

**ALWAYS** run this before every `git commit`:

```bash
npx tsc -p tsconfig.app.json --noEmit
```

This is the only command that activates `noUnusedLocals`, `noUnusedParameters`, `strict`, and all other checks from `tsconfig.app.json`.

## Additional rules

- When extending any union type (e.g. `VenueEmailType`, `ArtistEmailType`, `OutreachStatus`), immediately grep the entire codebase for `Record<ThatType` and update **every match** in the same commit. Missing a single `Record` entry is a build-blocking error.
- Each branch of a JSX ternary must return a **single root element** — wrap siblings in `<>...</>` if needed. Never place two sibling JSX elements inside one ternary branch.
- When removing a function, remove every variable or destructured import that was exclusively used by that function in the same edit.
